The evidence with the title 'Safety net funds: why traditional advice is wrong - betterment ' says Conventional wisdom says that a safety net fund should be held in a savings account or similarly risk - free asset. ... Think of it this way : Betterment's bond allocations have betas of 0.14 and -0.02 . A 30% stock/70% bond portfolio would therefore grow very slowly in a good economy , and drop very slowly in a bad economy . 
